than 31 December 2013, or </li><li>for which the integrated environment permit for town planning activities was granted over five years ago, and that meet the EPB requirements and for which the EPB declaration was submitted on time, or</li><li>under renovation for which the integrated environment permit was granted less than five years ago, if they were connected to the distribution grid before 2014. </li></ul><p>This premium is granted for new <strong>photovoltaic solar panels with an inverter power of up to 10 kVA</strong>. The expansion of an existing setup is not eligible. </p><p>The new solar panels must be installed on the roof of a building or validated by an <a href=\"https://rescert.be/nl/list?res_category=2\">installer with a certiﬁcate of competence (RESCert).</a></p><p>The solar panels <strong>must be installed on the roof of a building.</strong> If it is a heated building, the roof must also be insulated (Rd value of at least 3 m²K/W). Given the limited open space in Flanders, priority is given to the installation of a maximum number of solar panels on roofs. Consequently, premiums are only given for solar panels installed on roofs. </p><p>The<strong> premium runs from 1 January 2021 to the end of 2024.</strong> The date of commissioning (date of AREI inspection) of the solar panels determines the premium amount and requirements. </p><p>You can find all the requirements and details on the Dutch-language webpage ‘<a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/premie-van-fluvius-voor-zonnepanelen-op-gebouwen\">Premie van Fluvius voor zonnepanelen voor woongebouwen</a>’ (Fluvius premium for solar panels for residential buildings) </p>","nl-BE-x-formal":"<ul><li>De premie kan aangevraagd worden door natuurlijke personen en andere rechtspersonen (organisaties, vennootschappen, ….).</li><li>De premie geldt enkel voor gebouwen<ul><li>die <strong>aangesloten zijn op het elektriciteitsdistributienet van Fluvius uiterlijk op 31-12-2013</strong>,</li><li>of waarvoor de <